<!-- END APPRAISAL FORM -->
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      I know the western corridor well. Sumner's buyer profile is overwhelmingly family-driven: people who have outgrown a townhouse or smaller inner-suburban home and are now shopping for a proper backyard, a street where the kids can ride bikes, and a mortgage that does not require both parents to earn six figures. Understanding that buyer is the starting point for every campaign I run here.
    </p>
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:1rem; font-weight:300; line-height:1.8; color:#4a4540; margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The suburb's housing stock is predominantly brick homes from the 1970s and 1980s on blocks that range from 600 to over 800 square metres, with some larger lots in the quieter internal streets. The eastern edge carries some light industrial zoning, and buyers familiar with the suburb understand that the residential pockets well clear of Sumner Road are the ones that attract the best results. Centenary Motorway access is straightforward, making commute times to the CBD reliably manageable at approximately 25 minutes without traffic. Nearby Jindalee offers retail and dining, and Sinnamon Park shopping covers everyday needs. The result is a suburb that offers genuine space and quiet at a price point that still draws committed buyers.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Western Corridor Specialist</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Centenary corridor family market</p>
      </div>
      <div style="flex:1; min-width:200px; background:#fff; padding:1.75rem; border-left:3px solid #b98229; border-radius:16px;">
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.1rem; font-weight:400; color:#191817; margin-bottom:0.4rem;">Quiet Established Living</p>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.85rem; font-weight:300; color:#6b6560;">Generous blocks, family demand</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:0.82rem;color:#78716c;margin-top:2rem;">Also selling in: <a href="/suburbs/jindalee" style="color:#b98229;">Jindalee</a>, <a href="/suburbs/riverhills" style="color:#b98229;">Riverhills</a>, <a href="/suburbs/sinnamon-park" style="color:#b98229;">Sinnamon Park</a>.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===================================================
     SECTION: FAQ
==================================================== -->
<section style="background:var(--color-base, #f2ead4); padding:40px 24px 80px;">
  <div style="max-width:800px; margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.75rem; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:#b98229; margin-bottom:1rem;">FAQ</p>
    <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:clamp(1.8rem, 3.5vw, 2.8rem); font-weight:300; line-height:1.2; color:#191817; margin-bottom:2.5rem;">Common questions about Sumner.</h2>
    <div style="display:flex; flex-direction:column;">

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What drives property values in Sumner?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sumner's value is driven by its quiet residential character, generous block sizes and direct Centenary Motorway access. The suburb sits approximately 15 kilometres from the CBD, making it a practical choice for families who want space and lower prices than Jindalee or Sinnamon Park while maintaining good commute times. Well-presented family homes on flat, usable blocks consistently attract the strongest buyer competition.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          How long does it take to sell a home in Sumner?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Well-priced Sumner homes typically sell within 30 to 45 days. The suburb draws a practical family buyer pool from across the western corridor, and properties that are properly prepared and priced attract genuine competition. Homes with larger blocks and good street presentation sell at the faster end of that range.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(72,72,72,0.15); padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          What is the lifestyle like in Sumner?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sumner offers a quiet, established family lifestyle with the Centenary Motorway a short drive away for CBD commutes. The suburb is predominantly residential with some light industrial zoning at its edges, and the internal streets are peaceful with good tree coverage. Nearby Jindalee offers retail and dining options, and there is easy access to Sinnamon Park shopping and the western corridor generally.</p>
      </details>

      <details style="padding:1.25rem 0;">
        <summary style="font-family:var(--font-serif); font-size:1.05rem; cursor:pointer; color:#191817; list-style:none; display:flex; justify-content:space-between; align-items:center; gap:1rem;">
          Is Sumner a good suburb to buy in right now?
          <span style="color:#b98229; font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">+</span>
        </summary>
        <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans); font-size:0.9rem; line-height:1.75; color:#4a4540; margin-top:0.75rem; padding-right:2rem;">Sumner offers genuine value compared with Jindalee, Sinnamon Park and Riverhills for buyers who prioritise block size and quietness over suburb profile. It is a practical family suburb with stable demand and lower price points, which makes it an attractive entry into the western corridor for buyers whose budget does not stretch to the higher-profile addresses nearby.</p>
      </details>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

